msgid "reCAPTCHA Support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To safeguard registration against bots, {project_name} has integration with Google reCAPTCHA.\n"
"To enable this you need to first go to link:https://developers.google.com/recaptcha/[Google Recaptcha Website]\n"
"and create an API key so that you can get your reCAPTCHA site key and secret.\n"
"(FYI, localhost works by default so you don't have to specify a domain).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, there are a few steps you need to perform in the {project_name} Admin Console.\n"
"Click the `Authentication` left menu item and go to the `Flows` tab.  Select the `Registration` flow from the drop down\n"
"list on this page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Registration Flow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/registration-flow.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set the 'reCAPTCHA' requirement to `Required` by clicking the appropriate radio button.  This will enable\n"
"reCAPTCHA on the screen.  Next, you have to enter in the reCAPTCHA site key and secret that you generated at the Google reCAPTCHA Website.\n"
"Click on the 'Actions' button that is to the right of the reCAPTCHA flow entry, then \"Config\" link, and enter in the reCAPTCHA site key and secret on this config page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Recaptcha Config Page"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:{project_images}/recaptcha-config.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/users/recaptcha.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "The final step you have to do is to change some default HTTP response headers that {project_name} sets.  {project_name}\n"
"will prevent a website from including any login page within an iframe.  This is to prevent clickjacking attacks.  You need to\n"
"authorize Google to use the registration page within an iframe.  Go to\n"
"the `Realm Settings` left menu item and then go to the `Security Defenses` tab.  You will need to add `\\https://www.google.com` to the\n"
"values of both the `X-Frame-Options` and `Content-Security-Policy` headers.\n"
msgstr ""

